PGS correlation

This section shows the correlation between PGS in the reference sample. This is intended as a sanity check that the PGS correlations are in the expected direction, thereby confirming the GWAS alleles are being interpreted correctly.

Note. Plot shows correlation between pseudovalidated PGS in EUR population.

PGS coverage

This section summarises the polygenic score files, including both GWAS-derived and external scores. It reports the number of SNPs per score, the proportion present in the target sample, and the relative R accounting for missing variants. These metrics provide a check on score completeness, transferability, and the expected predictive utility in the target data.

Note. N SNP (non-zero) = Number of variants with non-zero effect in PGS; Mean missingness in target = Mean missingness of non-zero variants in target sample; Relative R2 = Estimated relative R2 of PGS in target sample given missing variants; N SNP overlap with LD reference = Number of non-zero variants present in LD reference data used to estimate relative R2.
